cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image segmentation using deep neural networks. The paper also involves training and testing of the segmentation and fusion modules, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of novel strategies for making full use of limited training data suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The evaluation of the framework on challenging abdominal organs suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep neural networks for segmentation suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
